  "notes": "Post Partum File 1 (4 PNC completion). Province/HUC rollup (5 rows; region skipped). 3 meta cols: psgc 0, constant 'NIR' filler 1, location NAME 2. CRITICAL RECOMPUTE (maternal_care_post_partum.md FLAG PP1-1): the source Excel 'completed' cells (cols 27/29/31) are cross-bracket shifted — 10-14 borrows 15-19's trans-in-done, etc. This config computes the CORRECT same-bracket sums (on-schedule + trans-in-done, same bracket), so the parser's completed values deliberately DIFFER from the source's buggy cells (e.g. NIR 10-14: parser 11 vs source 85). The total completion % is II/I (Completed/Tracked) despite the source's inverted '(I/II)' label. The source's own over-100% DQC is scale-broken (compares raw ratio to literal 100 — PP1-2); ours compares correctly. Annual sheet is a pure rollup, not ingested."
